  <description><![CDATA[<p>Luxury hotel in the heart of Vail Village offering great range of accommodation and amenities. The Sebastian was voted the top hotel in Vail and in top 100 hotels of the World. The hotel is known for its unique service and approach to creating home away from home. The Sebastian Hotel in not only defined by the fine art on the walls or the cobblestone atrium, but by the way they ensure that all your needs are met. The friendly and welcoming team will make sure your Vail and specailly Sebastian experience is Exceptional.</p>
<p>Some of the best Vail restaurants and dining options are right on property at The Sebastian - Vail, so that a great meal is never far away. Food and drink are an essential part of any mountain experience, as they keep the fun going long after the slopes are closed. Just as Vail Mountain offers something for skiers of all skills, so too does The Sebastian. With dining options for every palate and occasion, from a casual gathering with friends, to a celebratory family meal, to a romantic dinner for two, it seems the best place to dine in Vail is right here at home.</p>
<p>The dining options on-property are among the most tantalizing in all of Vail. Leonora, an Alpine Bistro &amp; Tapas Bar delivers world-class cuisine along with fine wines from around the world, the ultimate choice for a memorable meal or a lighter social session of tapas and wine. For casual fare, Market offers a quick, healthy breakfast or lunch in a café-style setting, the perfect option for grab-and-go aficionados. With an inviting atmosphere and amazing selection of beer, wine and spirits, Frost Bar is home to Vail’s finest throwback cocktails, perfect for après-ski or a nightcap before turning in. And of course, The Sebastian offers in-room dining on the occasions when staying home promises the best seat in town.</p>]]></description>
